caption: The food was delicious and they mastered in all their Dishes We even asked for spoon so we can get all the sauce on the dish. The pacing was very good too.!
So much delicious food and the staff went above and beyond for us while maintaining a clean and safe environment. As soon as I went home, I wanted to go right back. 😂

First time for us to get a Kit to be cooked at home. Their Linguini Seafood Kit was the best we’ve ever had! So flavorful!!! Pasta was just the right amount, seafood was fresh and the cream sauce was to die for! We’ve also had EggNog Pie and Cinnamon Rolls and both of it was really really good too! Last summer we’ve tried some pastries too which included croissants, cinnamon buns etc. and it’s the BEST here in Chicago! Travelle never fails to impress!

Fairly limited brunch menu, shrimp and grits were good

Amazing food and date spot with a calm and romantic atmosphere. Chef Vucko’s update menu is a treat for your taste buds with farm to table produce and proteins. Get a table by the kitchen if possible to see everyone in action.

Really great place, breakfast is to die for especially avocado toast. Great drinks! We also visited their bar in the evening hours their signature cocktails are must try, “London Lover” is #1 choice. Exceptional service, exceptional cocktails.
Delicious food and drinks. Wonderful and attentive service by Hugo. Travelle is one of my favorite places and I will be soon.

Amazing ambiance! Especially at night.... with the view of the Chicago river! The staff were amazing and helped choose our orders.

The bar is really sharp with comfortable seating options, a cool view over the Chicago River and nice service. Our meal was excellent. We enjoyed oysters, Asiago bread (spicy! spread), their unique take on a Caesar salad, plus a bone-in ribeye and Brussels Sprouts as a side. Everything was delicious and perfectly prepared. The view into the glass-walled kitchen was cool and the dining room is very nice. We'd definitely call Travelle a hidden gem and will be back!

We dined for breakfast at Travelle while staying at the Langham under the Amex fine hotels and resorts program.  They include breakfast for $50 dollars per person, which goes along way even with the high prices here.  We ordered lobster Benedict, bruschetta eggs, skillet cinnamon roll and mango chia seed pudding.  All were excellent with the standouts being the cinnamon roll and lobster Benedict.  The cinnamon roll was probably the best I have ever had!  Service was very good as well and we requested a nice table by the window.  Overall I would highly recommend Travelle for breakfast/brunch if you are staying at the hotel or in the area.

This is my second time going after work for a happy hour that turned in to spending several hours with coworkers and friends. We never felt rushed or like we had over stayed our welcome, but in fact the opposite! The waitress was so sweet and gave excellent recommendations - a fall burrata dish?! Must try! The space is perfect for enjoying a relaxing time with friends and of course the views can not be beat!
Great cocktails. Good food. Has a nice view and just a good lil spot to relax.
Food and service is good. Cool kitchen in glass box
Always great service and excellent food!
Beautiful building, great ambiance.
This restaurant provides amazing service as well as enjoyable menu. My favourite spot in the area. The drinks and food arrived rapidly and the rates were economical. I recommend this place.
Great views quality drinks.
Nice environment. Most beautiful waitress in the world.

Great food, service and drinks. Have a drink in the bar before dinner and enjoy the views and great service. Dinner is fantastic, had a small group and were lucky to sit in the wine/private room. Loved the whole fish! Friends had the tri tip, salmon, steak frites, wedge salad and the lobster risotto.  Had the meatballs and asiago bread as appetizers, both were good. Had sides of asparagus and tempura kabocha squash, delish. Winner of the night were the lobster risotto and the fish. Yum!
Amazing Christmas Brunch!!!
Great view.
The food was delicious. The service was exemplary. The visit was memorable.
The food a Travelle was top class! If you are looking for a place to dine with comfort and relaxation while gazing upon world class kitchen staff prepare you meal then this is the place.

Divine dining experience. Delightful dishes at down to earth prices. Wait staff took such great care of me. Comfortable elegant atmosphere that's not crowded and perfect noise level. This Chef is one to experience.
The water they serve tastes like sewage.  I can't believe this place misses an important detail like that. Just buy a water filter!
Enjoyable meal and experience from beginning to end.

The restaurant is romantically lit, quiet and beautiful. The staff really try to make you feel taken care of and knowledgeable on the menu.  Tl;dr - hidden gems: bread and pork butter (w/honey comb) and asparagus  Food: bread with pork butter, meatballs, 6oz filet mignon, and the coffee budino.  Drink: sparkling water and zinfandel ($21/glass)  The meatballs were served with toasted bread. The meatball itself was average but the toasted bread with the marinara sauce was a great combo.  The bread with pork butter - RECOMMEND! The bread is toasted and deliciously savory. Complimented with the pork butter that’s a bit spicy. Paired with honey comb! So good!  The filet mignon was served with some sort of flashed fried broccoli and tendon. The steak was tender and the broccoli added a wonderful crunch and flavor. Broccoli was quite delicious. It was crunchy, slightly salty, and just tasty.  I had their Zinfandel paired with my filet and that complimented nicely.  Macaroni and cheese was average. Crispy potato was good! The toppings are baked IN to the potato. Asparagus was crunchy and flavorful - hidden gem! RECOMMEND
A very friendly staff, great service, great food, great drinks! We can’t wait to come back!

Just dinned at travelle Chicago. We meet a distinguished gentleman named Marc silencieux. He cale to insure our din’ing Experience was excellent.  I’m glad to say they had by far surpassed any restaurant in area. Thanks Marc silencieux

Beautiful place and cozy atmosphere!  I am attaching a photo of a drink , I loved it ! Madison is such a nice girl , she was helping us out and she recommended me a drink !! Cozy atmosphere, delicious food , we had tartar and salmon poke !!

Wow, what an experience! I was here for a work conference and had a great time. Drinks were very well made and the appetizers served throughout the night were delicious. Staff was kind and friendly.
Great view, just enough people to feel lively after hours, really good food. Comfortable chairs and couches and a great view of the Chicago river. Very professional staff make this a favorite of mine

We visit this large and comfortable bar before heading to a show and it never fails to disappoint. It's rarely crowded; never loud. The sleek room is stunning--floor to ceiling windows provide panoramic views of the river and cityscape. The service couldn't be better and, most importantly, the cocktails are perfection. I haven't eaten at the restaurant for over a year, but I thought it, too, was excellent. Still, it's the bar that's the stunner for me.
Amazing drinks list fantastic ambiance and great views

I came here with colleagues after one of us had this bar recommended to her at an architecture boat tour. The guide had commented that it's a mad men type place. While it's certainly that time period, it's not at all dark and cozy. The travelle is in a van der Rohe building, which was originally built for IBM. The bar is on the 2nd floor, with a gorgeous view of the river. I recommend coming here for a drink at night, when the bar is gorgeously lit. The service is phenomenal. Our server was invested in making sure we had a great experience. She explained the cocktails and had great recs based on what liquors we told her we liked.
Great range of drinks and friendly staff
Good food, cool bar, nice people.
Great place for happy hour. Beautiful view of river.

We went for our anniversary and were very pleased. The melon soup, ahi tuna in rose water dashi, and asiago bread with pork butter and honey were fantastic. Though it’s $19, I can’t recommend the cocktail called One Night In Guadalajara enough.

Delicious a la carte breakfast with traditional and fancy options such as black seed chia coconut passion fruit and mango pudding. The playing and atmosphere is beautiful!

Whether a business or girls lunch, dinner or dinner and drinks at the bar across from the restaurant, the food is always on point (with great portions) and the atmosphere is comfortable. Servers carefully ask about food concerns or allergies and are always professional and attentive. I opted for the daily grilled cheese this day and could only eat half of the cheesy goodness on crusty bread that was cooked to perfection (with a salad of course!).
Awesome bar with great view, hip decor and ambiance. So, so restaurant.
The Langham is 5 star all the way !! I cannot stress enough..please book a night or two and pamper yourself !!

Two items of our lunch-for-two were 1-star (the review is plus one for service).  The steak tartar, while fresh, was barely edible. The meat was already salty. It also had capers. It also was generously sprinkled with sea salt. A nuclear combination - not in a good way.  Then we had what we asked to be Cacio e Pepe. It was not. If anything, it was Pasta Primavera with noodles on a softer side. Neither cheese nor pepper were prominent, yet green peas were abundant.  The floor manager checked how we were doing and took the two items off the bill, but that won't make us return.
Better views than food. However the bar staff is exceptional

Excellent service and cuisine combine to make for a memorable meal.  The atmosphere, being located on the second floor of the AMA HQ (Former IBM Building) is beautiful, and the neutral, clean lines of the dining room let you focus on the real star: the food.  Chef Jeff Vucko is backed by a rock-star team; together they produce memorable top notch food.  Highly recommended!

Went here for a quick cocktail. The list is pretty good and extensive. The waitress was amazing at explaining the drinks. The view over the river was amazing at night. Good seating and they served corn nuts and peanuts for a small snack. Would go back again.

The Langham may be my favorite hotel in Chicago.  We are not staying here on this trip to Chicago, we're here for a conference on someone else's dime, but we stopped in for a couple of drinks and a pre dinner bite.  The room is beautiful, with a great view.  The drink list is extensive, and the cocktails strong.  The loss of five stars is due to the gorgeous looking, but vapid staff, more into posing with each other, than helping the patrons.  The manager isn't hiring them for their gregarious nature and serving prowess. The staff looked more like the chorus line for the show "Chicago," than people working at a bar in Chicago.  I expected a leather pant, chain smoking, Bob Fosse to walk in yelling at the gathered staff, "Let's go people.  Let's see those kicks." The patrons were an after thought compared to their own narcissism.  Yet, this is a great splurge spot, reminiscent of Malibu, Santa Monica, and Brentwood. Carl Sandburg's "City of Big Shoulders" was nowhere to be found. Two glasses of wine, two cocktails, meatballs and bread equaled $100.00.  A bargain for such a display of banal beauty.

Moment your server(s) arrive, they welcome you by your name which you don't see much in restaurants. This really gave a warm and made it more of a personal welcome that puts them on another level from the rest. Great ambiance!
Beautiful hotel. Very nice rooms and employees. The restaurant has excellent chilaquiles.

A wonderful place to celebrate a birthday and/or just have lunch.  All the staff were great.  Our server made very good recommendations.  We had the express lunch, 3 courses with reasonable portions, a good value.  We had a beautiful complimentary dessert.  The hotel is also a favorite place for afternoon tea.  I highly recommend it.

Great date night dinner. Service was excellent and being able to see the chef through the glass kitchen was a neat experience. Food were delicious and the steak was one of the best that I've had. Highly recommend!

Good service, nice atmosphere and great selection of wine. Food was presented well, artic char was great. Short ribs brought the evening down...way too fatty. Staff quick to correct. One bad entree away from outstanding.
Second to none.
Great restaurant with great views of the river. The kitchen is surrounded by glass so you can see meals being prepared. Highly recommended!
Travelle never disappoints. Excellent food, ambience, & service. A true gem.

One of the perfect places in the world.  Being one floor above the foot traffic is like starting half a drink in.  David Rockwell's interior design respects and augments the Mies Van Der Roe building, the menu is simple, elegant (crab toast). comforting (meatballs) and tasty (everything), the drinks change with the seasons and are always marvelous.  Best of all, there is extremely low staff turnover with most of the staff in place for three or four years.  A perfect formula, perfectly executed by a perfect staff.  A tiny bit pricey, but in such elegant circumstances, who wants to eat or drink quickly?  The slightly high prices encourage you to savor every aspect.
Great views, beautiful decor for the holidays.
Best cocktails ever. Best service ever. Go here for a special time.
Food is great,service good,the manager mr ross umali was very accomodating...

I came here for dinner with a large group from work. The food was excellent in all aspects from the appetizers, to the main course as well as dessert. We had pan fried octopus as a appetizer which was wonderful. It was all a very elegant and enjoyable evening.

The food was amazing and the staff was so accommodating.  I had a wonderful time with friends. There was an odd moment when the waiter brought my drink and said, " it was alot of work to make this drink ".... but we laughed. No snarky comment was going to ruin our wonderful day. Thank you for a lovely time

An elegant experience, complete with sweeping views of the Chicago river as it winds its way down its most iconic stretch in downtown Chicago.  The food is truly excellent, the wine list more than complete, and the bartenders skilled at their craft.  On a recent visit a freshly-prepared barley risotto was expertly paired with a 2014 Nebbiolo.  Great experience, time and again.  A bit on the pricey side, but not crazily so.
We are generally skeptical about hotel restaurants but this one was a pleasant surprise. Food and service were both excellent.

Had an amazing time. The food was superb, as expected from such an establishment.  The wait staff and kitchen staff as a whole made sure we had a great evening. They handled a slight delay during service (they appeared short staffed during a portion of the evening) with professionalism, making us feel little to no inconvenience.  All in all, highly recommended and would visit again when in Chicago.

Awesome bar located inside The Langham hotel. This place is beautiful and has a very clean, elegant and upscale feel to it. I like that it is never very busy here and I’m always able to find a place to sit and enjoy my Paloma. They give you corn nuts and sweet peanuts to nibble on. This place is perfect for a date night or a drink with friends.
The food here is amazing. The view from the lounge area looks over the Chicago River public walk and statue garden. What a view!

My wife and I stopped in on a Wednesday evening while downtown for some business.  She had been raving about this place for some time now and that I absolutely needed to try it.  Our evening started off a little crazy with a few chewing gum mishaps and had to move a few tables.  It was a little unsetting but the manner of how the manger took care of us after was fantastic (didn’t catch his name – French gentleman wonderful attitude).  I must say my wife was indeed right… this place is phenomenal.  I enjoyed every bite and we will most definitely return.

I love this place. The ambience, location, food and people are great. I have not once been disappointed with any of the above. The last time I visited was for a farewell dinner for a friend and they gave us some complimentary champagne just because she was leaving. Love such warm places and people!

Excellent value for your $$ - brunch and 4-course Benefit for Green City Market Dinner Series (every Wednesday, menu changes weekly). SERVICE with grace and class!  Baked Beans in $35 off-menu LANGHAM BRUNCH flutters my heart and belly. Accompanying CARROT JUICE rocked my world of worthiness. Forgetabout common LA COLOMBE coffee.  Due to this wonderful experience, I am now a LANGHAM SUPPER CLUB member!  Say HELLO to Dawid and Carlos G! 😘😘
A hotel restaurant along the river. Service is excellent and I recommend the ceviche for a lighter dish and a flatbread to start.
Always great however for some reason their flat bread dough is so hard. It's as almost as hard the board.
Great food and great service
Friendly staff at the bar, and had great food recommendations. Loved the crab toast from the brunch menu. Also a beautiful atmosohere, with nice finishes.
Good atmosphere and even better food. The blueberry pancakes and the bruschetta eggs were the absolute best.
Overpriced. Very nice place, good service but good was just ok and very expensive.
Great stuff

If nothing else, plan on going to the lounge. Gorgeous views, comfortable, and stellar service and drinks.  We dined in the restaurant for the first time tonight and it exceeded my expectations. Maurico was knowledgeable and provided wonderful service. And the food? Simply amazing. Our group started w the empanadas and pork tostada, both of which were perfectly sized as starters. The mix of flavors in the tostada was so good.  Squash soup was pretty good but our entrees were at the level of the starters. Branzino was perfectly prepared and the risotto? Quite simply the best any of us had ever had.  We shared the cauliflower and the brussel sprouts, again, perfectly prepared and so flavorful.  The table we sat at managed to be both elegant and incredibly comfortable.  All in all one of the best dining experiences I've had.
Very good food, but gigantic portions in the breakfast, and only a la carte options. I do like to throw away food. Bedsides that the service is low! A lot of room for improvement
Great location and lounge. Only stopped in for a drink. The cocktails a creative and delicious
Great brunch, great waiters.

Absolutely amazing cocktails! The food is great and the staff is wonderful, accommodating and so polite. The restaurant is well put together and I definitely recommend stopping into this gem whether it just for drinks or dinner as well.
Its ok. Worse than the last time i went. Dinner is always better.
Loved the pork belly!
Biggest disappointment of my stay.  Smoke and mirrors cover for poor food.  Dried up and would not recommend.

Do believe the other reviews or the star rating. The old analogy comes to mind "don't judge by cover". It is smoke and mirrors. When coming to a place like this, i expected to be wowed. It was a big disappointment. I have made a better breakfast at home. The toast even came burnt to a crisp and they cook expected the public to eat it. I would like to know what he or her was thinking serving a charcoal briquets. If you don't mind wasting money, come here.
Delicious wine and American fare in an elegant hotel on the Chicago River. Try the lamb burger and the French 75!

I came here first for restaurant week where I had  Lemon tea- just ok Lemon thyme risotto - well made Minestrone soup with butternut squash soup - a bit meh Panna cotta grape jam - delicious  and then for dinner with a group of friends where I tried  drink: parisian memories - well mixed and interesting food: lamb tartare and peri peri chicken. the lamb was good, but the chicken didnt have the heat I was expecting, but it was well prepared (grilled) and tasted really good  The ambience is what people come for, though I personally dont really care for the views, too many buildings around all the windows. The wait staff is excellent, give good recommendations and are helpful. I was with a large group the second time around and they were happy to work around us, especially with the ones finishing their drinks and the late comers.  Also, definitely check out the lobby on the way to the restrooms, the hanging marbles are gorgeous. They also do a high tea in that area, will be back to check that out

The bar is just one of my favorite places in Chicago. Beautiful furniture designed by architect Mies van der Rohe, including the iconic Barcelona chair. Great view on the river. Ridiculous cocktails and impeccable service.

The service was stellar. The staff were very welcoming & made every effort to accommodate our special dietary needs. We are going back in a few weeks & are really looking forward to it. The atmosphere is warm, inviting, & quite relaxing
Really great food.  The watermelon gazpacho was amazing.  In fact ever dish we had was the bomb!

Sometimes one item can derail an entire dinner and change your impression of a restaurant completely. This is, or used to, be a great restaurant. Clearly the night we were there in August 2017 either the chef wasn't, or, the restaurant has simply slipped. Doesn't this sound delicious: "CRISPY THAI CHICKEN WINGS · peanuts, lime, fresh herbs?" Yes, it does. We ordered it, and the wings were hot on the outside and ICE COLD on the inside. Not just one, every single one we tried. Not as if they had been sitting too long and cooled, but instead because they had been frozen and not cooked well enough. A health threat and an unsettling feeling when you bite into that. So they apologized and returned soon with another one...surely the chef would know, and check, taste a wing, or use their thermometer...but no. Again, the hot wings were ice cold on the inside. Not sure who was cooking or what was wrong with the process, but it was a little disgusting. Everything else was delicious, but I just won't be able to return. And as an aside, to Travelle's management and to other restaurants who use the same tactic, when something goes wrong and you really want to make up for it...send the GM out, or the chef, apologize, try your best to make up for it...but offering a complimentary dessert after dessert was initially declined, and the check was requested, is not really a great way to apologize or ingratiate yourself to your guests.
I was there last week my hamburger was over cooked but the fries where the best .
Loved the Wednesday farmer's market Prix Fixe
Travelle immediately became a regular spot and I keep coming back. Beautifully presented, generous portions and wonderful staff.
Great cocktails, friendly staff and quiet tucked away seats
Diego is an awesome server! He told us all about the hotel and gave us a lot of great tips about things to do! He charred-tar is perfection. Loved my visit!
Great service and food.  Highly recommended
Swell location overlooking the Chicago River. Great service.
Excellent food, cocktails, champagne, ambiance and service!
Fantastic wait staff, great drinks, great food and not as over the top expensive as one might think for high end, downtown Chicago.
Exceptional service. I made a reservation and the hostess and server both referred me by name which I though was very welcoming and nice. Views and interior are beautiful. Great place for brunch.
One of the best high tea experiences!

I stopped by for breakfast and I understand why the Langham is known for having the best service. I was pampered from the moment I stepped in. My omelette was nothing special, but the fruit was perfectly ripe and the potatoes and gluten free toast were truly fantastic. It's pricey for sure, but it was a very relaxing 30 minutes with a view of the river.
We had the Farm Fresh menu which is offered on Wednesdays. Every dish was flavorful and delicious. It was also a great value with 4 dishes for $45.

Nice setting in an amazing Hotel but Travelle lets down the property, their food is OVER-SALTED a terrible practice often employed to sell more liquor.  The service was friendly but mediocre and the food was really a let down for a location like this.  Please overhaul it!
Good food. Slow service

Beautiful space with high ceilings and lots of light. We went for a Saturday brunch. There is an extensive buffet, but we ordered off the menu.  The skillet we had was good, but the highlight of the meal was the Benedict. We selected the salmon, and it was an amazing blend of ingredients. The sauce was not a standard Hollandaise as is usual on a Benedict, but rather something much more citrusy and a perfect accompaniment to the salmon and the beautifully cooked eggs. Wedge potatoes had a strong herb flavor but were unremarkable. Service was attentive.  It should be noted that, although we did not have wines (since it was 10am), the wine list here is perhaps the most interesting in the city, with a very broad range of selections ranging from extravagant to affordable, and all very interesting.
Impeccably furnished mid-century gem with a lounge overlooking the Chicago River. Service was gracious and the food theatrical. Our waitress was a supermodel from another planet.

NYE menu was not worth the cost, only enjoyed 3 of the 6 courses served. Service was ok when at the table but slow based on the number of open tables. The lobster bisque was thin and bitter, the beef tenderloin lacked flavor without the sauce. I did enjoy the risotto, pork belly, and dessert.
Eclectic nouveau-tropical cuisine that didn't quite click for me. Superb wine list, however.
Very impressed, overall. Love the sea-cuterie, and the flat bread with mushrooms and asparagus. Also the best salad isn't unique but it is delicious, nonetheless. The bean fries were skippable.

Don't go if your hungry. Friday dinner at this established and "talked about" place, but it was more fluff than good food. They had a "Chef's week" menu, which sound delicious, but they forgot to tell us that the portions were half size. Appetizers were fine, Pork belly and gazpacho soup - nothing to rave about, but solid. The soup was too milky and fruity for my taste. Entre: Halibut and Lamb chops. Two tiny, very thin lamb shops that had very little flavor and burned on the outside. This was not even an appetizer. halibut was okay, nice 4oz piece with small potatoes and a delicious sauce. But again, vey small. We mentioned the small portions to the waiter who offered to bring more food, we settled for coffee with the dessert, it arrived 15 minutes before the dessert. Oh well. Service was fantastic, and to their credit, they want to make it up for us. Overall is was a nice experience, but a restaurant is first and foremost about the food and we left hungry. Will we go back? Probably, I've heard they can do it right.
We went here for Chicago Restaurant week. The menu and value was terrific. The service was top notch. I thought the main dish (beef short ribs) could have used more salt and were a bit dry.

Travelle is the whole package.  Beautiful dining room with a pristine, lab-like kitchen visible behind glass; delicious food with expert preparation; and very personable service which is also personal and warm--no detail is overlooked, and no request is too small, so every diner feels like a VIP, no matter how fancy or casual the occasion.  The wine and cocktail selection leave nothing to be desired.   As with most hotel restaurants, a trip to the restroom requires a bit of a stroll, but the hotel's decor makes it a nice trip with plenty to look at along the way (including an adorable gift shop).  The bar/lounge on the same floor offers a limited food menu, but the same great drinks and unbeatable service.  I understand that they are/will be featuring a special cocktail of the week or month demo in the coming months (a new program that the talented and creative bartenders are looking to try out), so I look forward to a return visit in the coming months.

I came here with my Fiance as a celebratory dinner and it was absolutely perfect! The manager Dawid provided the best service we have both ever experienced at a restaurant. Everyone knew we were recently engaged and made us feel very special. The food was phenomenal as well but the service was incredible.

Came here with a friend for her birthday dinner. Everyone was nice and knew a lot about the food they served. Decor is very classy and pleasing to the eye. The food was outstanding as well. Finding a parking in that area is hard.
Excellent food.

Came here with my parents for Christmas brunch.  First off, the hotel is GORGEOUS!  The decor is modern and chic, just like me hehehe  Anyways, the dining room wasn't full, but I think this was intentional as it was the holidays and the experience is partly due to the full attention of the wait staff (which we had).  Our server was wonderful (I forgot his name).  We had the prix fix menu and everything was wonderful.  I loved how the dessert cakes were presented on a cart, and later plated with a beautiful presentation.  The spiked rum was warm and rich, a perfect ending to our meal.  I definitely want to come back and try the a la carte menu.

Great food. The chicken wing presentation is pretty cool. The white wine was good as well. Went on two separate occasions. One for lunch and one for a evening birthday party. Both were pleasant experiences.  The bottles of champagne are very reasonably priced. The live violinist is AWESOME!! She was playing top 40 songs and it was a great vibe. I'd go back just to see her play.
Sat at the chefs table for dinner and it was fantastic!  Seacuterie (5chef), flaming chicken wings and mixed vegetables were excellent.

I came here on lunch for a special celebration and had a wonderful experience!  Staff is very attentive and helpful in guiding you through their menu.  The space is decorated beautifully - very modern.  I had a burger and it was absolutely delicious.  Everything was cooked perfectly and just the right portion.  The chef sent out a dessert that wasn't on the menu in honor my celebration which was such a nice touch.  I would love to come back to try their dinner menu and see the night time views of the city!
